    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-05T07:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-05T07:41:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Netherlands/52: Telegram (part air)</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-05T13:00:00+00:19"
                            >December 5, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 6—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>88. Department’s telegram No. 47, October 8, 6 p.m. Commander Thompson and I
                    discussed question this morning with various Netherlands authorities including
                    Minister of Finance. Commander Thompson submitted memorandum copy of which is
                    being forwarded to the Department.<note n="83" xml:id="d325fn83">Not
                        printed.</note> Despite my efforts to keep conversation on an informal basis
                    the Minister of Finance indicated that an official communication would be
                    necessary.</p>
                <p>In view of the present inactivity of the port of Rotterdam in connection with the
                    shipments in question does the Department still wish me to make formal request
                    of the Netherlands Government to consider the extension of the existing
                    provision covering small ships (100 tons and under) to include all vessels
                    carrying spirits to any other country.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
